<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="422">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181873" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavifrons Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavifrons Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavifrons">Pheidole flavifrons</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="422">Types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="422">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181873" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavifrons Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavifrons Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavifrons">flavifrons</taxonomicName>
, yellow front, pertaining to the anterior half of the major's head.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="422">
Diagnosis A medium-sized, uniquely multicolored member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33744" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole flavens Roger" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole flavens Roger" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavens">flavens</taxonomicName>
group, whose major has a prominent, subangular humerus and exclusively carinulate head, and the minor has a dentate humerus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="422">
Most similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33595" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arhuaca">arhuaca</taxonomicName>
of Colombia but with different color, and in the major a smooth (not foveolate) pronotal dorsum; and to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181838" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole amazonica Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole amazonica Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica">amazonica</taxonomicName>
, differing in head sculpture and shape of humerus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="422">
See also the less similar 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33875" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole minutula Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole minutula Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutula">minutula</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181913" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole nitidicollis Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole nitidicollis Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidicollis">nitidicollis</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:34045" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tenerescens Wheeler" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tenerescens Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenerescens">tenerescens</taxonomicName>
, and other species listed as close to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33595" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole arhuaca Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arhuaca">arhuaca</taxonomicName>
(q.v.). Measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.86, HL 0.92, SL 0.44, EL 0.10, PW 0.44. Paratype minor: HW 0.44, HL 0.48, SL 0.40, EL 0.08, PW 0.28.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="422">Color Major: anterior half of head yellow, posterior half yellowish brown, with a dark brown circular spot in the center of the head capsule dorsum; body medium brown, mandibles and scape light brown, rest of appendages yellow. Minor: body dark brown; appendages, clypeus, and anterior genal margins yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="422">range Known only from the type locality in Amazonian Peru.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="422">Biology The type series was taken from beneath the bark of a tree in a terra firme tree fall.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="422">figure Upper: holotype, major. Lower: paratype, minor. PERU: Cuzco Amazonico, 15 km northeast of Puerto Maldonado, Madre de Dios (Stefan Cover and John E. Tobin). Scale bars = 1 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
